The '''Kilmodan Carved Stones''' are a group of West Highland carved grave slabs exhibited in a burial aisle within [[Kilmodan Church|Kilmodan Churchyard]], [[Clachan of Glendaruel]], within the [[Cowal]] Peninsula, [[Argyll and Bute]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.historic-scotland.gov.uk/propertyresults/propertydetail.htm?PropID=PL_182 |title=Property Detail |publisher=Historic-scotland.gov.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-04-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.britainexpress.com/attractions.htm?attraction=4771 |title=Kilmodan Sculptured Stones &#124; History, Travel, and accommodation information |publisher=Britainexpress.com |date= |accessdate=2012-04-07}}</ref> They are in the care of [[Historic Scotland]].
